-- Coal Exports From Australia's Newcastle Port Rise as Ship Queue Shortens
-- B y   B e n   S h a r p l e s
-- 2010-10-19T01:28:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-19/coal-exports-from-australia-s-newcastle-port-rise-as-ship-queue-shortens.html
Coal shipments from Australia’s
Newcastle, the world’s biggest export harbor for the power-
station fuel, increased 27 percent last week while the queue of
vessels waiting to load shortened.  The volume of the commodity exported in the week ended 7
a.m. local time yesterday climbed to 2.38 million metric tons
from 1.87 million in the preceding period, Newcastle Port Corp.
said on its website today.  Rio Tinto Group ,  Xstrata Plc  and BHP Billiton Ltd. are
among mining companies that ship the fuel from the harbor, which
has three export terminals. Twelve vessels were outside the
port, down from 13 a week earlier, while the waiting period
averaged 13.92 days, compared with 13.78, the report said.  Power-station coal prices at Newcastle, an Asian benchmark,
gained 2.1 percent, according to the  globalCOAL  NEWC Index
website. Prices advanced to $96.91 a ton in the week ended Oct.
15, from $94.95 in the previous period.  To contact the reporter on this story:
